      • addRangeCondition

        public <T extends Comparable<T>> PartitionFilter.Builder addRangeCondition(String field,
                                                                  @Nullable
                                                                  T lower,
                                                                  @Nullable
                                                                  T upper)
        Add a condition for a given field name with an inclusive lower and an exclusive upper bound. Either bound can be null, meaning unbounded in that direction. If both upper and lower bound are null, then this condition has no effect and is not added to the filter.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the partition field
        Parameters:
        field - The name of the partition field
        lower - the inclusive lower bound. If null, there is no lower bound.
        upper - the exclusive upper bound. If null, there is no upper bound.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the field name is null, empty, or already exists, or if both bounds are equal (meaning the condition cannot be satisfied).

      • addValueCondition

        public <T extends Comparable<T>> PartitionFilter.Builder addValueCondition(String field,
                                                                  T value)
        Add a condition that matches by equality.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the partition field
        Parameters:
        field - The name of the partition field
        value - The value that matching field values must have
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the field name is null, empty, or already exists, or if the value is null.
